9 Jun 96

readme.ms, user.c:
If the value of seed fed to asa_seed() is less than 0, this signals the
default randflt() to initialize the array of seeds to be shuffled.
This is especially useful when using repeated calls to asa_main() when
ASA_LIB is TRUE.

